trans-unit.source: When used as a resource key for a data template, allows the data template to participate in the lookup process.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref> class with the specified template type.
This constructor is protected.
A <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey.TemplateType"></xref> value that specifies the type of this template.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref> class with the specified parameters.
This constructor is protected.
A <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey.TemplateType"></xref> value that specifies the type of this template.
The type for which this template is designed.
Gets or sets the assembly that contains the template definition.
The assembly in which the template is defined.
Gets or sets the type for which the template is designed.

The <xref href="System.Type"></xref> that specifies the type of object that the template is used to display, or a string that specifies the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] tag name for the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xml-md.md)] data that the template is used to display.
Returns a value that indicates whether the given instance is identical to this instance of <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref>.
The object to compare for equality.
`true` if the two instances are identical; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code for this instance of <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref>.
The hash code for this instance of <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref>.
Returns a string representation of this <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref>.
A string representation of this <xref href="System.Windows.TemplateKey"></xref>.
This member supports the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_winclient](~/includes/tlasharptla-winclient-md.md)] infrastructure and is not intended to be used directly from your code.
